Ans:Based on the line chart above, residential electricity usage went up in 2020 from August to December comparing to the data from 2018 and 2019. There seems to be a sharp increase in residential electricity usage in 2017 between August and October.

Ans: Based on the line chart above, residential gas usage in 2020 is about the same as the rest of the years with a slight increase from late October to December. There is a sharp increase in gas usage between August and October in 2017.

*ANS: For both residential and commercial electricity and gas usage, the general trend is similar for pre-pandemic and covid era. Both Commercial and Residential use more gas in the winter and more electricity in the summer. In the 2017-2020 data, I did not distinguish the various years in my data. As a result, variations in certain months of years can be mask by the chart. We assume that monthly data are similar among these years in this case.
